@startuml
' @id(SEQ-ELEMENT-DESC)
' @ref(USE-ELEMENT-DESC)
'
' Objective-side flow: selecting a diagram element shows its @desc text
' in the right-hand MODEL CONTEXT card, distinctly styled.
'
' @desc(SEQ-ELEMENT-DESC, "How the viewer resolves the @desc text for a selected @id and renders it as a distinct description block in the MODEL CONTEXT card.")
title Show a diagram element's description (objective)

actor "Developer" as Dev
participant "MddViewer\n(eframe::App)" as Viewer
participant "ModelRegistry\n(mdd-core)" as Reg
participant "DescIndex\n(@desc per @id)" as Desc
participant "MODEL CONTEXT card\n(right SidePanel)" as Card

Dev -> Viewer : select an element / @id\n(rail, IDs list, or graph node)
Viewer -> Reg : file + ids for selection
Reg --> Viewer : selected @id
Viewer -> Desc : description_for(@id)
note right of Desc
  @desc(<ID>, "text") markers are extracted
  from the model file at registry build time,
  same pass as @id/@ref. One description per
  significant element. Missing -> card shows
  "No description" (a /mdd-validate readiness
  warning, not a hard error).
end note
Desc --> Viewer : description text (or none)

Viewer -> Card : render distinct DESCRIPTION block\n(above IDS / TRACE sections)
Card --> Dev : element description shown

opt no @desc for the selected id
  Viewer -> Card : render weak "No description"
  Card --> Dev : placeholder
end
@enduml
